                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 European War 1939/6704: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Consul at Leopoldville</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Mallon</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-11-18T18:00:00-05:00"
                            >November 18, 1940—6 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Your November 17, 2 p.m. Department has no objection to your accompanying High
                    Commissioner on proposed trip in a purely personal capacity. Naturally you will
                    be guided in this and in any similar situation in the future by the Department’s
                    telegraphic instructions of September 7, in which you were cautioned to avoid
                    any statement or action which might in any way commit this Government.</p>
                <p>Please report results of your trip by telegraph.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Welles</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
